WEBVTT

00:19.584 --> 00:22.848
- Hey, hey, buddy.
My battery died, man.

00:22.892 --> 00:25.112
You think
you can give me a jump?

00:25.155 --> 00:27.679
- I don't have any cables.
- Oh, I do.

00:29.594 --> 00:31.770
- Yeah, whatever.
- Thank you.

00:31.814 --> 00:32.771
Thank you, man.

00:32.815 --> 00:34.164
If you just wanna
pop your hood.

00:34.208 --> 00:38.734
I'll grab my cables.

00:41.780 --> 00:44.087
- Ah!
Ow, ah!

00:49.179 --> 00:51.312
- Nighty night.

00:51.355 --> 00:53.749
[tense music]

00:53.792 --> 00:56.578
- [gasps]

00:56.621 --> 00:58.841
Where--
where am I?

01:00.190 --> 01:01.800
What's going on?
- Shh, shh, shh.

01:01.844 --> 01:03.280
Hey, hey, hey.

01:03.324 --> 01:06.588
Now, we don't want anybody
to hear, right?

01:06.631 --> 01:09.199
I mean, this is
our little secret.

01:09.243 --> 01:10.505
- Who are you?

01:10.548 --> 01:12.115
- Ah, you'll have plenty
of time to remember

01:12.159 --> 01:16.598
while we play our game.
Highway 66 is a mile south.

01:18.252 --> 01:21.646
I'm gonna give you
a three-minute head start.

01:23.605 --> 01:27.435
Today is the day.

01:28.958 --> 01:31.439
You're not
the predator anymore.

01:31.482 --> 01:33.615
You're the prey.

01:36.792 --> 01:41.362
That's 2 minutes, 56 seconds.

01:41.405 --> 01:42.667
You're wasting time.

01:42.711 --> 01:45.714
- [grunting]

01:50.849 --> 01:53.809
[tense music]

01:53.852 --> 02:00.859
♪

02:04.776 --> 02:07.823
- Help!
Anyone!

02:07.866 --> 02:09.825
Someone help!

02:09.868 --> 02:16.875
♪

02:32.674 --> 02:33.675
[gunshot]

02:33.718 --> 02:35.155
[whimpers]

02:36.286 --> 02:37.287
[gunshot]

02:39.028 --> 02:40.638
- Just getting your attention.

02:40.682 --> 02:44.555
- Please don't kill me!
I'll do whatever you want!

02:44.599 --> 02:48.777
- Well, I want you to run.
I want you to be scared.

02:48.820 --> 02:50.996
I want you to know
there's no escape.

02:51.040 --> 02:55.914
♪

02:55.958 --> 02:57.612
[gunshot]

02:57.655 --> 03:04.662
♪

03:13.367 --> 03:16.239
- Hey!
Did you just shoot my Jeep?

03:23.812 --> 03:25.640
Oh, God.

03:27.772 --> 03:28.947
[gunshot]

03:32.951 --> 03:35.911
[tense music]

03:35.954 --> 03:39.567
♪

03:41.569 --> 03:43.353
- Under, nice.
Finish.

03:43.397 --> 03:45.399
Finish strong, come on.

03:45.442 --> 03:46.965
Come on, finish strong.
Come on, come on!

03:47.009 --> 03:49.359
- Ah!
- [chuckles]

03:49.403 --> 03:51.753
How you feel?
- Amazing.

03:51.796 --> 03:53.885
I am tired, like, really tired.

03:53.929 --> 03:55.147
If I sat down, I don't think

03:55.191 --> 03:58.281
I'd be able
to stand back up, but amazing.

03:58.325 --> 03:59.978
- You know what?
You got good technique though.

04:00.022 --> 04:02.067
- Oh, thanks.
You're just being nice.

04:02.111 --> 04:03.895
I can't believe
you get the train down here

04:03.939 --> 04:05.506
from Washington Heights
every morning.

04:05.549 --> 04:06.855
- I like this gym.

04:06.898 --> 04:08.378
It reminds me of the one
I used to train at in LA.

04:08.422 --> 04:09.423
- Oh.

04:10.902 --> 04:13.035
- I must have walked past here,
like, 100 times,

04:13.078 --> 04:14.471
and I never noticed it.

04:14.515 --> 04:15.777
- The old Hana
walked past here,

04:15.820 --> 04:18.997
not the New Hana.

04:19.041 --> 04:22.436
You know,
I was thinking pasta tonight.

04:22.479 --> 04:25.090
Puttanesca sauce,
a side of Caesar.

04:25.134 --> 04:27.397
- You're cooking again?
- Is that a bad thing?

04:27.441 --> 04:28.616
- Oh, hell no.

04:28.659 --> 04:30.313
I mean, Crosby was
my roommate for a year,

04:30.357 --> 04:32.054
and he cooked maybe once.
- [laughs]

04:32.097 --> 04:33.664
- I'm glad you moved in.

04:33.708 --> 04:34.926
- Me too.
You know what?

04:34.970 --> 04:36.145
Let's stop by the store

04:36.188 --> 04:37.451
and get some fresh bread
on the way home.

04:37.494 --> 04:39.757
[phone beeps]

04:39.801 --> 04:41.759
- Oh, groceries gonna
have to wait.

04:41.803 --> 04:43.370
- Yep.

04:44.458 --> 04:45.937
- Found the bodies
two hours ago.

04:45.981 --> 04:48.418
Didn't want to move 'em
till you got here.

04:48.462 --> 04:51.073
Victim in the tree line
is Jamie Scott, local hunter,

04:51.116 --> 04:54.598
owner of this Jeep.
Shot once in the back.

04:54.642 --> 04:56.339
The victim over here
is a different story.

04:56.383 --> 04:59.429
Hope you've had
your coffee already.

04:59.473 --> 05:03.346
♪

05:03.390 --> 05:05.392
- Decapitated.

05:05.435 --> 05:08.743
- Have you found the head?
- Not yet.

05:08.786 --> 05:10.353
Wallet was still on the body.

05:10.397 --> 05:13.400
The name is John Clemons.
Address here is in Pittsburgh.

05:13.443 --> 05:14.662
- Any shell casings?

05:14.705 --> 05:17.926
- Uh, four in total
off of a .308.

05:17.969 --> 05:20.494
The Jeep was hit twice.
Jamie was hit once.

05:20.537 --> 05:21.886
Not sure where
the fourth one went.

05:21.930 --> 05:23.366
- I hate to say it,

05:23.410 --> 05:25.586
but it could be
in this guy's missing head.

05:25.629 --> 05:27.979
- One-shot through the trees
at a moving target.

05:28.023 --> 05:29.981
Our unsub's a marksman.

05:30.025 --> 05:32.027
- Yeah, but Clemons
was the intended target.

05:32.070 --> 05:34.508
He took the time to cut off
his head and take it with him,

05:34.551 --> 05:36.074
maybe as some kind of trophy.

05:36.118 --> 05:38.381
- Hunter had the bad luck
of walking up on it.

05:38.425 --> 05:39.643
Wrong place.
Wrong time.

05:39.687 --> 05:41.689
- It's a damn shame.

05:41.732 --> 05:44.126
Jamie was a good man.
He didn't deserve this.

05:44.169 --> 05:45.649
- The hunter had a GoPro

05:45.693 --> 05:46.998
attached
to the brim of his hat.

05:47.042 --> 05:48.478
The batteries are dead,
but I'll be able

05:48.522 --> 05:50.001
to pull footage
and maybe see what happened.

05:50.045 --> 05:51.742
- Okay, good.

05:51.786 --> 05:53.918
- Okay, I got something.

05:53.962 --> 05:56.399
John Clemons
is a registered sex offender.

05:56.443 --> 05:58.096
Ten years ago,
he was convicted of molesting

05:58.140 --> 06:00.708
a 12-year-old boy
named Chris Preston.

06:00.751 --> 06:02.753
He went to prison
and got out six months ago

06:02.797 --> 06:04.581
and went home to Pittsburgh.

06:04.625 --> 06:07.758
Chris Preston's last known
and current address

06:07.802 --> 06:09.630
are also in Pittsburgh.

06:09.673 --> 06:11.458
- Sounds like
a hell of a motive.

06:11.501 --> 06:13.808
- All right, Hana and Barnes,
head to the MCC

06:13.851 --> 06:15.766
and start digging in.

06:15.810 --> 06:17.551
The rest of us
will go see Chris Preston.

06:21.511 --> 06:22.904
- How did you meet John?

06:22.947 --> 06:24.514
- He was transferred
to our troop

06:24.558 --> 06:26.864
when I was 11
to become scoutmaster.

06:26.908 --> 06:28.866
Troop 88212.

06:28.910 --> 06:31.913
He seemed nice at first,

06:31.956 --> 06:36.570
helped me build a compass,
and, um...

06:36.613 --> 06:38.746
then on a camping trip once...

06:44.186 --> 06:47.537
Look, he was
a sick pervert, okay?

06:47.581 --> 06:49.800
And he got what he deserved.

06:49.844 --> 06:51.193
- Considering the nature
of the crime

06:51.236 --> 06:52.412
and what he did to you...

06:55.980 --> 06:57.417
- You think that I killed him?

06:57.460 --> 07:01.072
- I think whoever did had
a deeply personal reason to.

07:05.033 --> 07:07.209
Did you know John had
gotten out of prison?

07:07.252 --> 07:10.560
- Yeah, I knew.

07:10.604 --> 07:12.562
I'm not gonna lie to you, okay?

07:12.606 --> 07:16.566
I thought about it...a lot.

07:16.610 --> 07:18.046
But I didn't do it.

07:18.089 --> 07:20.483
Besides, I was working here
last night till closing.

07:20.527 --> 07:23.094
My boss can confirm it.

07:23.138 --> 07:24.966
- Okay.
We'll talk to her.

07:26.228 --> 07:28.230
- Two days ago,
I, uh--

07:28.273 --> 07:31.146
I got this letter
from a lawyer.

07:31.189 --> 07:34.671
It's about the class-action
lawsuit against the Boy Scouts.

07:34.715 --> 07:37.631
- "Law Offices of Nedra Lewis."

07:37.674 --> 07:39.937
- Skip to the last paragraph.

07:39.981 --> 07:41.852
She says
with a special case like mine

07:41.896 --> 07:44.507
that I could get up to $15,000.

07:44.551 --> 07:47.031
- What, for everything
that happened to you?

07:47.075 --> 07:49.033
- Look, you tell me
what's worse, okay,

07:49.077 --> 07:51.775
being told that your trauma
doesn't matter,

07:51.819 --> 07:54.822
or that it's only worth 15K?

07:54.865 --> 07:56.301
- Do you know of any other kids

07:56.345 --> 07:59.522
who might
have been abused by John?

07:59.566 --> 08:02.525
- It wasn't a secret.

08:02.569 --> 08:03.657
The older kids in the troop,

08:03.700 --> 08:05.746
they used to call his tent
the bear cave.

08:05.789 --> 08:08.139
Like, somewhere
it wasn't safe to be.

08:08.183 --> 08:12.970
Everyone knew.

08:13.014 --> 08:16.278
Everyone except me, I guess.

08:18.846 --> 08:20.369
- Hey, boss.

08:20.412 --> 08:23.111
Hana has the footage ready
from the hunter's GoPro camera.

08:25.592 --> 08:28.551
- Hey!
Did you just shoot my Jeep?

08:30.858 --> 08:32.860
Oh, God.

08:35.732 --> 08:37.255
[gunshot]
Ah!

08:44.045 --> 08:45.525
- Freeze it there.

08:46.917 --> 08:48.092
- Yeah, I see it.

08:48.136 --> 08:50.225
He has some kind
of scarring on his hand.

08:50.268 --> 08:52.096
- Okay, I'll do a screen grab
and add it

08:52.140 --> 08:53.750
to the description
of our unsub.

08:53.794 --> 08:55.317
- Anything new on Clemons?
- Yeah.

08:55.360 --> 08:56.753
I found out he was
a troop leader

08:56.797 --> 08:58.363
in the Boy Scouts.

08:58.407 --> 09:02.890
- Scoutmaster for Troop 88212,
which Chris Preston was in.

09:04.021 --> 09:06.023
- Okay, not just that one.

09:06.067 --> 09:08.025
He was in charge of two others
before that.

09:08.069 --> 09:10.767
- That's a lot of other kids
he'd have been in contact with.

09:10.811 --> 09:12.029
- Keep digging.

09:12.073 --> 09:14.336
Oh, there's a lawyer
suing the Boy Scouts.

09:14.379 --> 09:16.207
We're gonna see what she knows.

09:16.251 --> 09:17.905
- Tuesday's no good.

09:17.948 --> 09:20.255
No, I have the Sanctuary Choir
event that night.

09:20.298 --> 09:22.692
Oh, that could work.
I'll have to check with Dan.

09:22.736 --> 09:23.998
I got to go.
Okay.

09:24.041 --> 09:25.608
I'll see you at devotional
in the morning--

09:25.652 --> 09:29.307
[screaming]

09:29.351 --> 09:33.703
- It seems to be a pattern.
[sighs]

09:33.747 --> 09:35.400
That's what's so depressing.

09:35.444 --> 09:39.840
The men targeting these boys
were often reassigned

09:39.883 --> 09:42.233
when claims of abuse
were made against them.

09:42.277 --> 09:43.670
- So what,
they just shuffled abusers

09:43.713 --> 09:45.019
around like
the Catholic Church?

09:45.062 --> 09:46.934
- Yeah, that's the allegation
we're making.

09:48.239 --> 09:50.111
- And did the church here
know about Clemons?

09:50.154 --> 09:53.941
- Oh, according to the evidence
I've seen, absolutely.

09:53.984 --> 09:56.073
There's no telling
how many more kids

09:56.117 --> 09:57.684
he would have had access to

09:57.727 --> 09:59.860
if not
for Chris Preston's bravery

09:59.903 --> 10:01.905
in going to the police
with his story.

10:01.949 --> 10:04.255
- Have any more of Clemons'
victims come forward?

10:04.299 --> 10:05.474
- A few.

10:05.517 --> 10:09.826
We sent a mailer
to all the former members

10:09.870 --> 10:13.090
we could find
he had interactions with.

10:13.134 --> 10:15.397
Hopefully, more will join in.

10:15.440 --> 10:17.268
- So--so they come forward,

10:17.312 --> 10:19.793
and they expose
their trauma to the world,

10:19.836 --> 10:23.927
and they get $15,000
or less in return?

10:23.971 --> 10:27.409
I can see why they might
not take you up on that.

10:27.452 --> 10:29.672
- Is the amount
anywhere close to appropriate?

10:29.716 --> 10:30.978
Of course not.

10:31.021 --> 10:33.371
It doesn't begin
to represent the pain

10:33.415 --> 10:37.245
these kids have been through,
but it is an acknowledgment

10:37.288 --> 10:38.899
that what happened
to them was real,

10:38.942 --> 10:42.119
and it wasn't their fault.

10:42.163 --> 10:46.297
Hopefully, that is a step
in the direction of healing.

10:46.341 --> 10:48.778
- Well, I'd like to see
that mailing list please.

10:48.822 --> 10:50.954
- Oh, fair warning,
there are over 450 names

10:50.998 --> 10:53.435
on here
and a lot of John Does.

10:53.478 --> 10:55.959
It's going to take a while
to print out.

10:58.135 --> 11:01.312
- Now, you're getting
a five-minute head start.

11:01.356 --> 11:03.227
That's generous.

11:03.271 --> 11:05.142
And it's gonna be dark in 20.

11:05.186 --> 11:07.014
- [muffled sobbing]

11:07.057 --> 11:08.145
- Come on, even I can't hit

11:08.189 --> 11:09.669
a moving target
in the pitch black.

11:11.801 --> 11:14.282
So, Courtney,

11:14.325 --> 11:16.110
here's the important part.

11:16.153 --> 11:19.461
If you can stay
ahead of me for 20 minutes,

11:19.504 --> 11:23.726
you survive.
- [muffled sobbing]

11:23.770 --> 11:26.033
It's scary, isn't it?

11:29.384 --> 11:31.995
Being alone in the woods
with a predator?

11:32.039 --> 11:34.345
Being helpless to fight back?

11:34.389 --> 11:38.045
- Why are you doing this?
Who are you?

11:39.786 --> 11:42.310
- You know, fact that you
don't know says everything.

11:45.226 --> 11:46.923
But you...

11:48.882 --> 11:50.884
- [gasping]

11:50.927 --> 11:53.234
- You knew who John Clemons
was, though, didn't you?

11:55.932 --> 11:59.196
You best get running.

11:59.240 --> 12:00.850
You're burning daylight.

12:03.984 --> 12:06.943
[tense music]

12:06.987 --> 12:13.994
♪

12:18.346 --> 12:19.913
- The ranch foreman
was walking the fence line

12:19.956 --> 12:21.871
this morning and found her.
- What kind of ranch is that?

12:21.915 --> 12:23.917
- Canned hunting for deer.

12:23.960 --> 12:26.528
The fence keeps them in
so they're easier to find.

12:26.571 --> 12:27.921
Their property butts right up
against the national forest

12:27.964 --> 12:30.575
all through here.
- There's blood on the fence.

12:30.619 --> 12:32.621
- She could have been trying
to climb over

12:32.664 --> 12:35.493
when she got shot,

12:35.537 --> 12:38.540
dragged over here.
Any shell casings?

12:38.583 --> 12:40.455
- Haven't found any,
or the head.

12:40.498 --> 12:42.326
- It's not from a gunshot.

12:42.370 --> 12:43.632
- What's that?

12:43.675 --> 12:45.460
- It doesn't look
like a gunshot.

12:45.503 --> 12:48.593
- Oh, you're right.

12:48.637 --> 12:52.423
- A rifle would have caused
a larger exit wound.

12:52.467 --> 12:53.642
- We have an ID yet?
- Yeah.

12:53.685 --> 12:55.775
Prints are a match
to Courtney Parker.

12:55.818 --> 12:58.821
Her husband, Dan, reported
her missing early this morning.

12:58.865 --> 13:00.475
- Any chance she's
a registered sex offender?

13:00.518 --> 13:01.650
- Not at all.

13:01.693 --> 13:02.999
She was director
of youth ministries

13:03.043 --> 13:05.349
at her church, nothing
but upstanding on paper.

13:05.393 --> 13:08.439
- Hey, boss, I found an arrow
with blood on it.

13:09.919 --> 13:12.748
- Our killer's changed
his MO.

13:12.792 --> 13:14.402
- Tailoring it
to each of his victims?

13:14.445 --> 13:15.838
- Maybe.

13:15.882 --> 13:18.058
When was the last time
Courtney was seen alive?

13:18.101 --> 13:20.625
- She was at her church
until 3:00.

13:20.669 --> 13:21.844
- So that's--

13:21.888 --> 13:23.715
- It's two hours
from Pittsburgh.

13:23.759 --> 13:25.456
- Gets dark
around about 5:30.

13:25.500 --> 13:27.894
It's awful hard to make a shot
with a bow and arrow

13:27.937 --> 13:29.069
when you're losing that light.

13:29.112 --> 13:30.592
- That makes the hunt
more difficult.

13:30.635 --> 13:31.854
He's challenging himself.

13:31.898 --> 13:33.769
- The question is,
"Why this victim?"

13:33.813 --> 13:36.903
Why don't you grab Hana,
canvass local archery stores,

13:36.946 --> 13:40.602
see if we can find out
where that arrow comes from?

13:40.645 --> 13:43.474
Kristin and I will go see
this poor woman's husband.

13:44.867 --> 13:48.131
- Courtney's so dedicated.
She was always busy.

13:48.175 --> 13:50.525
Always working late.

13:50.568 --> 13:54.137
It's not unusual for me to go
to sleep before she gets home.

13:54.181 --> 13:57.532
When I woke up this morning
and she wasn't here,

13:57.575 --> 13:59.403
I realized something was wrong.

14:01.188 --> 14:04.104
- How long was your wife
involved with the church?

14:04.147 --> 14:06.541
- Over 25 years.

14:06.584 --> 14:09.631
She did community outreach,
prayer groups,

14:09.674 --> 14:12.852
oversaw the youth choir,
church sponsorships.

14:12.895 --> 14:16.899
It wasn't a job to her.
It was her heart.

14:16.943 --> 14:19.902
- And what--what kind
of sponsorships?

14:19.946 --> 14:22.078
- Food pantries,
clothing drives,

14:22.122 --> 14:24.602
even local scout troops.

14:24.646 --> 14:26.082
- Troop 88212?

14:26.126 --> 14:29.042
- Yeah, I think
that was one of them.

14:29.085 --> 14:32.654
There were several
over the years.

14:32.697 --> 14:34.090
- Did she know John Clemons?

14:38.094 --> 14:41.010
- No.
Not personally.

14:41.054 --> 14:44.100
- But she did know him?
- And what he did?

14:45.101 --> 14:46.973
- Not at the time.

14:47.016 --> 14:49.976
These lies that she was aware
of what that man did

14:50.019 --> 14:53.980
or that she--that she helped
cover it up, they're absurd.

14:54.023 --> 14:55.590
She didn't know about him.

14:55.633 --> 14:57.505
- There's a lawsuit
that claims otherwise.

14:57.548 --> 14:59.942
- Well, that lawsuit
is a cash grab.

14:59.986 --> 15:00.987
They have people coming forward

15:01.030 --> 15:04.729
who never even met
John Clemons.

15:04.773 --> 15:06.514
Courtney was a victim too.

15:06.557 --> 15:08.037
Her name was dragged
through the mud.

15:08.081 --> 15:10.605
Her reputation
was almost ruined.

15:10.648 --> 15:13.956
- I understand,
but clearly someone believed

15:14.000 --> 15:16.916
that she was involved
in covering up Clemons' abuse.

15:19.005 --> 15:21.921
- Someone murdered my wife,

15:21.964 --> 15:24.662
killed her like an animal
in the woods,

15:24.706 --> 15:27.970
and you are supposed
to be finding the monster

15:28.014 --> 15:33.715
that did this, not persecuting
my dead wife over slander.

15:33.758 --> 15:34.803
Get out.

15:34.846 --> 15:37.806
[tense music]

15:37.849 --> 15:43.072
♪

15:43.116 --> 15:45.727
[eerie music]

15:45.770 --> 15:50.732
[rattling]

15:50.775 --> 15:57.739
♪

15:57.782 --> 16:00.785
- [grunting]

16:00.829 --> 16:03.832
[gasping]

16:15.670 --> 16:17.106
- I need your help
with something.

16:19.065 --> 16:21.545
- Please, please, please,
just let me go.

16:21.589 --> 16:23.025
- No, stop crying.

16:23.069 --> 16:26.115
It's not gonna change anything,
all right?

16:26.159 --> 16:28.074
You know, my dad
used to tell me that.

16:29.118 --> 16:32.034
- Please.
Whatever you want.

16:39.215 --> 16:40.564
- Pick one.

16:40.608 --> 16:47.615
♪

16:54.883 --> 16:56.276
Thank you.

16:56.319 --> 16:59.018
- A mean son of a bitch
fired this thing.

16:59.061 --> 17:01.063
- What makes you say that?

17:01.107 --> 17:03.587
- This arrowhead's
heavily modified.

17:03.631 --> 17:08.070
The edge has been barbed
and serrated.

17:08.114 --> 17:12.248
It's meant to take chunks
out of whatever organ it hits.

17:12.292 --> 17:15.077
Maximum damage.
Maximum suffering.

17:15.121 --> 17:17.819
These are highly illegal
in Pennsylvania

17:17.862 --> 17:19.647
'cause they're inhumane.

17:19.690 --> 17:20.909
- Do you know where somebody

17:20.952 --> 17:22.171
could get
an arrowhead like that?

17:22.215 --> 17:25.914
- These are pretty
standard professional grade,

17:25.957 --> 17:29.048
but the fletching here...
let me see.

17:30.223 --> 17:32.181
These are real turkey feathers.

17:32.225 --> 17:34.879
They're custom and handmade.

17:34.923 --> 17:37.621
There it is.
9.5.

17:37.665 --> 17:40.102
That's Wally's mark.
- Who's Wally?

17:40.146 --> 17:43.671
- Wally Turner, he's a guide
at the ranch down the road.

17:43.714 --> 17:46.065
Great hunter.
- The Bradshaw Ranch?

17:46.108 --> 17:48.980
- Yeah.
Wally fletches his own arrows.

17:49.024 --> 17:51.809
I contract him time to time
to do some for the shop.

17:51.853 --> 17:54.856
He always marks his work
with the number 9.5.

17:54.899 --> 17:57.685
That's the points
of his first state record kill.

17:57.728 --> 17:59.426
- Does he have scarring
on his right arm?

17:59.469 --> 18:05.127
- Yeah, some accident
when he was a kid.

18:05.171 --> 18:06.998
- Do you know where he lives?

18:07.042 --> 18:08.826
- Just down the road
in a cabin.

18:08.870 --> 18:11.438
It's right outside the ranch.

18:11.481 --> 18:14.789
[dramatic music]

18:14.832 --> 18:21.361
♪

18:36.854 --> 18:38.160
- Clear in here.

18:38.204 --> 18:42.860
- We got
a deer rifle over here.

18:42.904 --> 18:45.472
- We got a bow, some arrows.

18:45.515 --> 18:48.910
Could be our murder weapons.

18:52.261 --> 18:54.872
Somebody's been using
this sleeping bag.

18:59.007 --> 19:02.837
Fresh blood.
We just missed him.

19:03.925 --> 19:07.102
- You need to come outside.
We found something.

19:16.894 --> 19:18.331
Oh, God.

19:18.374 --> 19:21.334
- Clemons and Courtney.
- What's left of 'em.

19:21.377 --> 19:23.336
- I've seen this before
at hunt camp.

19:23.379 --> 19:25.164
It's nature's
most efficient way.

19:25.207 --> 19:27.209
The insects will clean
the skulls naturally,

19:27.253 --> 19:28.732
and then
you've got your trophies.

19:28.776 --> 19:30.952
- It's still disgusting.

19:30.995 --> 19:33.302
- Our fugitive isn't
hunting animals anymore.

19:33.346 --> 19:35.304
He's hunting human beings,

19:35.348 --> 19:36.871
and judging by the blood

19:36.914 --> 19:40.048
in the sleeping bag
back there...

19:40.091 --> 19:42.442
he's already found
his next victim.

19:48.796 --> 19:52.016
- Our fugitive
is Walter "Wally" Turner.

19:52.060 --> 19:53.975
Age 28, no criminal history,

19:54.018 --> 19:56.107
and no family outside
of his parents in Kittanning.

19:56.151 --> 19:58.414
- And I spoke to his manager
at Bradshaw Ranch,

19:58.458 --> 20:00.764
says Wally is
the best guide he has.

20:00.808 --> 20:02.288
His schedule
usually stays full,

20:02.331 --> 20:03.289
but he hasn't booked
a trip in weeks.

20:03.332 --> 20:04.551
They haven't seen him.

20:04.594 --> 20:05.943
- Is he close
with any of his co-workers?

20:05.987 --> 20:09.512
- No, manager says
he's quiet and a loner mostly.

20:09.556 --> 20:11.471
He just loves to hunt.

20:11.514 --> 20:12.950
- No friends, no family,

20:12.994 --> 20:15.475
no one to pay attention
to his comings and goings.

20:15.518 --> 20:18.347
- We have a make and model
on a truck registered to him.

20:18.391 --> 20:21.089
The BOLO's already out.
- Okay, I just found this.

20:21.132 --> 20:24.701
Wally Turner,
member of Boy Scout Troop 88212

20:24.745 --> 20:27.400
from 2001 to 2003.

20:27.443 --> 20:29.793
John Clemons
was his scoutmaster.

20:31.055 --> 20:33.667
- All right, so Turner
was abused by Clemons,

20:33.710 --> 20:36.452
and he blamed Courtney for
allowing Clemons to stay on

20:36.496 --> 20:40.064
as scoutmaster despite
allegations against him.

20:40.108 --> 20:42.763
- And then he killed them both
for what they did to him.

20:42.806 --> 20:44.155
- Now he can go after
anyone else

20:44.199 --> 20:46.593
he blames for his abuse.

20:46.636 --> 20:49.073
- We have PD protecting
the local council, right?

20:49.117 --> 20:51.467
- Yes, but Wally's already
taken another victim.

20:51.511 --> 20:54.775
- It's possible his rage might
not be limited to the council,

20:54.818 --> 20:58.518
so we need to figure out
who else he might target.

20:58.561 --> 20:59.867
Call Kristin.

20:59.910 --> 21:01.695
Let's start
with Turner's parents.

21:01.738 --> 21:04.567
- Sorry, we only
have dairy creamer.

21:04.611 --> 21:06.569
- Oh, that's fine.
Thank you.

21:06.613 --> 21:09.746
- Have either of you
seen Wally recently?

21:09.790 --> 21:12.096
- He came by a few weeks ago
to pick up his mail.

21:12.140 --> 21:15.491
It still comes
to the house here.

21:15.535 --> 21:18.059
- May I ask about Wally's scars
on his right hand?

21:18.102 --> 21:19.713
How'd he get those?

21:19.756 --> 21:22.629
- He got lost
during a Boy Scout camping trip

21:22.672 --> 21:25.762
when he was ten.
His scoutmaster--

21:25.806 --> 21:27.634
- John Clemons.
- Yes.

21:27.677 --> 21:30.463
Mr. Clemons said that Wally
just ran off from camp

21:30.506 --> 21:32.552
in the middle of the night.

21:32.595 --> 21:34.162
- How long was he alone
in the woods?

21:34.205 --> 21:36.643
- Almost two days.

21:36.686 --> 21:38.906
While he was out missing,
he ran up against

21:38.949 --> 21:43.214
this plant.
What's it called, Colton?

21:43.258 --> 21:46.696
- Hogweed.
The sap is poisonous.

21:46.740 --> 21:49.743
- He got it on his hand
and arm somehow.

21:49.786 --> 21:51.092
The doctor said
it was the equivalent

21:51.135 --> 21:52.659
of third-degree burns.

21:52.702 --> 21:54.922
- How much longer
did he stay in the troop?

21:54.965 --> 21:57.881
- Oh, he never went
back after that.

21:57.925 --> 22:00.406
They lost him in the woods.
What good were they?

22:00.449 --> 22:03.409
- They didn't lose him.
He run off.

22:06.934 --> 22:08.152
- Did Wally ever talk

22:08.196 --> 22:10.633
about why he might
have run off that night,

22:10.677 --> 22:13.114
or whether Clemons
was inappropriate with him?

22:13.157 --> 22:14.594
- Inappropriate?

22:14.637 --> 22:17.161
- That Clemons
abused him sexually?

22:18.293 --> 22:19.947
- No. Wally ain't no sissy.

22:19.990 --> 22:21.296
He wouldn't do
anything like that.

22:21.340 --> 22:23.603
- With all due respect,
he was ten years old.

22:23.646 --> 22:24.995
He wouldn't have had
much choice.

22:25.039 --> 22:27.694
- No, we heard about
those allegations of Clemons

22:27.737 --> 22:30.784
being a fruit, but Wally isn't.
- They weren't allegations.

22:30.827 --> 22:33.264
Clemons was convicted
of molesting one of the boys.

22:33.308 --> 22:36.093
- Those kinds of kids
that that stuff happens to,

22:36.137 --> 22:37.617
they send out signals.

22:37.660 --> 22:39.270
I read an article
on the internet,

22:39.314 --> 22:40.576
and our son
didn't put out any signals.

22:40.620 --> 22:41.969
- Are you trying to tell us--

22:42.012 --> 22:44.058
- Did you ever take Wally
to speak to a professional

22:44.101 --> 22:45.625
about his experience?

22:45.668 --> 22:47.714
- The detective
who worked Wally's case

22:47.757 --> 22:50.586
suggested we take him
to speak to a doctor.

22:50.630 --> 22:52.109
He gave us a card.

22:52.153 --> 22:53.720
Colton didn't think
it was necessary.

22:53.763 --> 22:55.025
- Wally ain't a nutcase.

22:55.069 --> 22:56.244
Going to a shrink
is like going to a mechanic.

22:56.287 --> 22:57.854
You tell him you think
something's wrong,

22:57.898 --> 22:59.247
and they're happy
to prove you right,

22:59.290 --> 23:01.162
charge you an arm
and a leg in the process.

23:01.205 --> 23:03.251
- You said Wally
still gets his mail here.

23:03.294 --> 23:06.254
Did he receive a letter
recently regarding a lawsuit?

23:06.297 --> 23:08.212
- Yes, he did.

23:09.562 --> 23:12.260
He got really angry about it.

23:12.303 --> 23:13.957
- What was it that
made him angry?

23:14.001 --> 23:16.830
- He said it was disgusting
that they'd try to lump him in

23:16.873 --> 23:19.920
with all these other kids.
- And he was right to be angry.

23:19.963 --> 23:22.792
It's a bunch of greedy people
looking for free money.

23:22.836 --> 23:24.272
Things happen.

23:24.315 --> 23:25.926
You can't just put your hand
out and expect the world

23:25.969 --> 23:29.320
to give you anything for it.
It's just the way things are.

23:29.364 --> 23:32.323
[tense music]

23:32.367 --> 23:36.153
♪

23:36.197 --> 23:37.807
- Can you believe those people?

23:37.851 --> 23:39.679
I mean, even if Wally
had told them about his abuse,

23:39.722 --> 23:40.897
they would have done nothing.

23:40.941 --> 23:42.246
How could you do that
to your own son?

23:42.290 --> 23:45.598
- Excuse me.
I just remembered something.

23:46.860 --> 23:48.557
I did take Wally to see
a psychiatrist

23:48.601 --> 23:50.907
a couple of times.

23:50.951 --> 23:53.257
Wally was different
after being lost.

23:53.301 --> 23:55.216
It was like a light
had gone out in him.

23:58.349 --> 24:00.917
Here's the doctor's card.
I saved it.

24:00.961 --> 24:04.530
- Thank you.
- I'll call it into Jess.

24:05.966 --> 24:07.184
- I remember Wally.

24:07.228 --> 24:10.187
He was ten, I believe,
at the time.

24:10.231 --> 24:13.190
He was at a campsite
and ran off

24:13.234 --> 24:16.193
into the woods shirtless
in the middle of the night.

24:16.237 --> 24:18.108
- We believe
that he was sexually abused

24:18.152 --> 24:20.720
by his scoutmaster,
John Clemons.

24:20.763 --> 24:22.852
- I do too.

24:22.896 --> 24:25.681
He exhibited all the signs.

24:25.725 --> 24:28.205
He was quiet,
emotionally withdrawn,

24:28.249 --> 24:30.207
anxious in closed spaces.

24:30.251 --> 24:31.731
Even being here alone
in this office

24:31.774 --> 24:33.384
was too much for him.

24:33.428 --> 24:36.779
We had to conduct the sessions
across the street in the park.

24:36.823 --> 24:38.781
- And did he ever admit
that he was abused?

24:38.825 --> 24:41.044
- No, he talked
about the forest,

24:41.088 --> 24:42.916
about how bad
the sap hurt his arm,

24:42.959 --> 24:46.180
but he would never talk about
what happened at that campsite.

24:46.223 --> 24:48.704
- And did you tell his mother
what you suspected?

24:48.748 --> 24:51.011
- Well, I tried,
but she wouldn't hear it.

24:51.054 --> 24:52.621
She said the Boy Scouts

24:52.665 --> 24:54.841
wouldn't put kids
in danger like that.

24:57.060 --> 24:59.628
- If he never opened up to you
about his abuse,

24:59.672 --> 25:01.804
he probably never
opened up to anybody.

25:01.848 --> 25:03.458
- No, I doubt it.

25:03.502 --> 25:07.157
He repressed the memory and all
the emotions attached to it,

25:07.201 --> 25:10.160
but the right trigger could
bring them all to the surface.

25:10.204 --> 25:11.771
- Something like a letter

25:11.814 --> 25:14.730
saying that your trauma
is worth $15,000?

25:14.774 --> 25:17.124
- Yeah, that could
absolutely do it.

25:17.167 --> 25:19.735
Now, Wally's
not my patient anymore.

25:19.779 --> 25:21.084
I've haven't seen him in years,

25:21.128 --> 25:25.915
but I can imagine
all the repressed emotion

25:25.959 --> 25:29.397
hitting him all at once
would be overwhelming.

25:29.440 --> 25:32.705
- Did he ever mention
anyone besides Clemons to you?

25:32.748 --> 25:34.968
Someone else he might blame?

25:35.011 --> 25:39.102
- No, but in my experience

25:39.146 --> 25:42.323
most victims
fall into cycles of trauma.

25:42.366 --> 25:46.022
Wally's cycle might not be
perpetuating sexual abuse

25:46.066 --> 25:49.460
but rather the feelings
that the abuse caused in him.

25:49.504 --> 25:51.854
- He's the predator
exerting dominance

25:51.898 --> 25:54.422
and control over the victims.

25:54.465 --> 25:59.383
- In my opinion, Wally's trying
to find closure in his own way.

25:59.427 --> 26:04.214
He made his abuser
feel powerless and scared.

26:04.258 --> 26:06.826
[phone rings]

26:06.869 --> 26:08.392
- Excuse me a second.

26:11.308 --> 26:13.136
Hey, Kristin.

26:13.180 --> 26:16.444
- I get what you're saying,
but he didn't stop there.

26:16.487 --> 26:20.056
- Correct, whatever closure
looks like to Wally,

26:20.100 --> 26:23.059
he's not stopping
until he gets it.

26:23.103 --> 26:24.408
- Forensics just ID'd

26:24.452 --> 26:26.759
some blood
from Wally's trailer.

26:26.802 --> 26:29.109
It belongs to a Cameron Early,

26:29.152 --> 26:31.981
another registered
sex offender.

26:32.025 --> 26:34.114
You have any idea
who he might be?

26:34.157 --> 26:35.855
- No,
but I doubt it's a coincidence

26:35.898 --> 26:38.466
that he's
a convicted sex offender.

26:41.382 --> 26:43.123
- You picked well, Cameron.

26:43.166 --> 26:45.473
You know, most people
don't consider

26:45.516 --> 26:47.475
statutory rape a crime,

26:47.518 --> 26:49.738
especially if
both people are young.

26:49.782 --> 26:52.175
You--you were 19, right?

26:52.219 --> 26:55.004
- It was consensual.
Her parents ratted us out.

26:55.048 --> 26:56.832
- Mm-hmm.

26:56.876 --> 27:00.053
Now, molesting a 12-year-old,

27:00.096 --> 27:01.837
yeah, I think everyone

27:01.881 --> 27:04.231
can agree that's
a despicable thing to do.

27:04.274 --> 27:06.189
- It's lies, man.
It's all lies.

27:06.233 --> 27:09.018
- No, it wasn't.

27:09.062 --> 27:11.847
See, I read all about you.

27:11.891 --> 27:14.720
- I don't know who you are,
but if you don't let me go,

27:14.763 --> 27:16.939
I will seriously mess you up.

27:18.288 --> 27:21.030
- I like your confidence.
You know what?

27:21.074 --> 27:23.859
It's only fair for you
to pick this time, okay?

27:23.903 --> 27:26.557
So pick a hand.

27:26.601 --> 27:28.734
- I'm not gonna play whatever
screwed-up game this is.

27:28.777 --> 27:31.388
[whimpers]

27:31.432 --> 27:35.392
- You heard me.
Come on, pick one.

27:41.529 --> 27:43.357
That's a good choice.

27:45.620 --> 27:48.884
And for you...

27:48.928 --> 27:52.453
okay, now,
the rules are simple.

27:52.496 --> 27:56.239
The first one of you to make it
to the foreman's office wins,

27:56.283 --> 27:57.806
is free to go.

27:57.850 --> 28:01.244
And the loser...yeah, well,

28:01.288 --> 28:05.292
the loser gets
exactly what they deserve.

28:07.468 --> 28:12.255
I'm gonna give you
a minute head start.

28:15.955 --> 28:18.914
[tense music]

28:18.958 --> 28:25.965
♪

28:30.621 --> 28:33.973
Oh, yeah, and, uh,
look out for an Easter egg.

28:34.016 --> 28:40.893
