29:00.173 --> 29:03.045
[gunshots]

29:04.960 --> 29:06.092
[gunshots]

29:06.135 --> 29:08.834
- [gasping]

29:08.877 --> 29:10.487
- Sorry, man.
Nothing personal.

29:10.531 --> 29:11.532
[gunshot]

29:21.542 --> 29:24.545
Ah-ah! Ah!

29:26.547 --> 29:28.941
Ahh!

29:28.984 --> 29:31.987
[sobbing]

29:34.947 --> 29:37.210
No!
No!

29:41.301 --> 29:44.217
No!
No!

29:47.002 --> 29:49.004
- I win.

29:52.921 --> 29:55.489
- First victim here
is Cameron Early.

29:55.532 --> 29:57.708
- It's our man
from the sleeping bag.

29:57.752 --> 29:59.710
- Based on the rigor, I'd say
he's been here all night.

29:59.754 --> 30:01.712
Shot first in the leg,
then again to the chest.

30:01.756 --> 30:03.845
Shell casing
is from a .38 revolver.

30:03.889 --> 30:05.151
- That's new.

30:05.194 --> 30:07.022
Our fugitive
hasn't used a handgun yet.

30:07.066 --> 30:09.982
- I don't think it was him.
Second victim's this way.

30:10.025 --> 30:11.853
- There's another one?

30:11.897 --> 30:14.725
- Yeah. We found two sets
of cut zip-ties

30:14.769 --> 30:15.901
near the front of the mill.

30:15.944 --> 30:17.554
Based on the footsteps,
it looks like

30:17.598 --> 30:19.992
they started there
and then came this way.

30:20.035 --> 30:22.864
This is one Matthew Pitts.

30:22.908 --> 30:25.040
His prints were in the system
and also on that gun.

30:25.084 --> 30:26.650
I figure he shot Early

30:26.694 --> 30:28.609
on the catwalk
and then ran in here.

30:28.652 --> 30:30.872
- So Pitts killed Early,
and then Turner killed him?

30:30.916 --> 30:33.005
- Well, that's what
it looks like.

30:33.048 --> 30:35.442
- Any connection between
Turner and these two?

30:35.485 --> 30:37.487
- They're both
registered sex offenders,

30:37.531 --> 30:39.750
but I'm not seeing a connection
to the Boy Scout camp.

30:39.794 --> 30:41.883
- And I doubt you'll find one.

30:41.927 --> 30:43.929
The Clemons and Courtney kills
were personal.

30:43.972 --> 30:45.931
He wanted them to feel
the terror that he felt,

30:45.974 --> 30:48.498
helpless and lost in the woods.

30:49.760 --> 30:54.461
This--this is a game.
He's escalated in every way.

30:54.504 --> 30:56.115
Two victims, not one.

30:56.158 --> 30:57.899
A steel mill
instead of the woods.

30:57.943 --> 31:00.597
- He even gave them a gun
to fight back with.

31:00.641 --> 31:02.077
- You mean to fight over.

31:02.121 --> 31:03.731
You've only found
the one gun, right?

31:03.774 --> 31:06.647
- Yes, sir.
- It's like the old joke.

31:06.690 --> 31:09.171
If you and a friend are running
from a bear in the woods,

31:09.215 --> 31:10.956
you don't have to be faster
than the bear,

31:10.999 --> 31:12.566
just faster than your friend.

31:12.609 --> 31:14.611
- So why these two?

31:14.655 --> 31:16.962
- His personal targets
may be done,

31:17.005 --> 31:20.139
but he certainly is not.

31:20.182 --> 31:24.143
The hunts gave him a sense
of power, and he likes it.

31:25.361 --> 31:27.755
These two were probably
picked at random.

31:27.798 --> 31:29.931
He didn't take their heads
as trophies.

31:29.975 --> 31:33.282
He hunted them like animals,
and he enjoyed killing them.

31:33.326 --> 31:36.590
He'll keep going
until we stop him.

31:36.633 --> 31:38.984
- Take a look at this.
- What is that?

31:39.027 --> 31:40.942
- It's every registered
sex offenders

31:40.986 --> 31:42.683
in Allegheny County.

31:44.206 --> 31:46.730
- He's got quarry for days.

31:46.774 --> 31:49.733
[tense music]

31:49.777 --> 31:56.784
♪

32:01.615 --> 32:02.964
- Are you Watkins Farr?

32:03.008 --> 32:06.098
- Wrong guy.
- Nah, I don't think so.

32:06.141 --> 32:08.665
Oral copulation
by fear or force

32:08.709 --> 32:12.843
of a nine-year-old boy, right?
Is that what you did?

32:12.887 --> 32:15.063
- What's your problem, man?
- You.

32:15.107 --> 32:17.848
You're my problem, Watkins.

32:17.892 --> 32:20.851
[tense music]

32:20.895 --> 32:22.853
- Oh!
Oh!

32:22.897 --> 32:27.684
♪

32:27.728 --> 32:29.077
- Turner already struck again?

32:29.121 --> 32:30.861
- In broad daylight
half an hour ago.

32:30.905 --> 32:32.776
- And he made no attempt
to hide the abduction.

32:32.820 --> 32:35.170
- No.
- You know who the victim is?

32:35.214 --> 32:36.737
- Watkins Farr.

32:36.780 --> 32:38.695
Store manager
knows him as a regular.

32:38.739 --> 32:41.002
- Let me guess,
another convicted sex offender?

32:41.046 --> 32:42.351
- Served 12 years in prison

32:42.395 --> 32:44.571
for molesting
a nine-year-old boy.

32:44.614 --> 32:45.964
- State police got a hit
on Turner's truck

32:46.007 --> 32:47.791
outside of a diner
in Blairsville.

32:47.835 --> 32:49.663
- This is more escalation.

32:49.706 --> 32:51.839
He's abducting his victims
in public now.

32:51.882 --> 32:53.797
- And making no attempt
to hide his truck.

32:53.841 --> 32:56.148
Either he's sloppy
or more brazen.

32:56.191 --> 32:58.193
- That makes him
more dangerous.

32:58.237 --> 33:00.935
Scramble state police.
Have 'em meet us at the diner.

33:08.725 --> 33:10.945
Check the diner.
I'll clear the truck.

33:19.910 --> 33:21.782
The truck is clear.

33:24.959 --> 33:27.222
- Stop that car!
- Stop that vehicle now!

33:27.266 --> 33:28.397
Stop it!
- He's running!

33:28.441 --> 33:29.920
Hold the line!
- FBI!

33:32.662 --> 33:36.623
Get out of the vehicle.
Put your hands in the air.

33:36.666 --> 33:38.146
Nice and slow.

33:43.108 --> 33:47.895
♪

33:51.899 --> 33:52.856
- I just came to check
on my patient.

33:52.900 --> 33:54.206
He said he needed me.

33:54.249 --> 33:56.512
- Turner is a fugitive
who's killed four people,

33:56.556 --> 33:58.166
and how is he
a patient of yours

33:58.210 --> 34:01.300
if you haven't seen him
in over two decades?

34:01.343 --> 34:02.649
- A year ago, I was invited

34:02.692 --> 34:05.521
to go hunting
at the Bradshaw Ranch.

34:05.565 --> 34:07.828
Wally was our guide.
- So you reconnected.

34:07.871 --> 34:09.656
- Yes, and he was struggling.

34:09.699 --> 34:10.918
It didn't take a professional

34:10.961 --> 34:12.876
to see that he
was in deep pain.

34:12.920 --> 34:14.574
I worked with him,
and just as it seemed

34:14.617 --> 34:18.186
we were getting somewhere,
he stopped coming.

34:18.230 --> 34:19.753
- Until last week.

34:19.796 --> 34:22.582
He came to see you after
he killed Clemons, didn't he?

34:22.625 --> 34:23.844
- Yes.

34:23.887 --> 34:25.498
- Did he tell you
he killed Clemons?

34:25.541 --> 34:28.631
- He didn't have to.
I could see it in him.

34:28.675 --> 34:31.982
He was free in a way
I'd never seen a patient.

34:32.026 --> 34:33.245
- You know, by doing this,

34:33.288 --> 34:34.420
you've impeded
an FBI investigation.

34:34.463 --> 34:36.030
- Not true.

34:36.074 --> 34:38.380
I'm only obligated to disclose
if he talks about committing

34:38.424 --> 34:39.947
a future crime,
which he did not.

34:39.990 --> 34:43.211
- You knew he wasn't
gonna stop, though, didn't you?

34:43.255 --> 34:44.908
- [sighs]

34:44.952 --> 34:46.910
- Why did he ask you
to meet him here?

34:46.954 --> 34:49.739
Did he ask you
to bring him something?

34:49.783 --> 34:51.915
- A hunting rifle and ammo.

34:51.959 --> 34:54.701
He knows you're after him,
and he says he's not scared.

34:54.744 --> 34:56.964
- Did you gave it to him?
- Yes.

34:57.007 --> 35:00.446
Yes, because Wally's right.

35:00.489 --> 35:01.925
These pedophiles,
they're not people anymore.

35:01.969 --> 35:03.623
They can't be reformed.

35:03.666 --> 35:07.540
I've spent 30 years
trying to heal the devastation

35:07.583 --> 35:09.585
they leave behind,
and I'm sick of it.

35:09.629 --> 35:13.328
- Secondary trauma can have
the same effects as PTSS.

35:13.372 --> 35:14.808
I think you're suffering
from it.

35:14.851 --> 35:16.375
- Maybe I am.

35:16.418 --> 35:19.029
All these years, all these
innocent children left broken.

35:19.073 --> 35:20.640
I don't care anymore.

35:20.683 --> 35:23.730
What Wally's doing feels
like justice for these victims!

35:23.773 --> 35:25.297
- It's not
Wally's justice to serve.

35:25.340 --> 35:28.038
- Yes, it is!

35:28.082 --> 35:31.564
I'm at peace with it.

35:31.607 --> 35:33.696
- Where did he go, Doctor?

35:35.002 --> 35:36.960
- He's in the woods
behind the diner.

35:37.004 --> 35:39.006
He--he's got a man with him.

35:39.049 --> 35:42.923
[radio chatter]

35:42.966 --> 35:44.359
- You're under arrest

35:44.403 --> 35:46.840
for aiding and abetting
a felon.

35:46.883 --> 35:49.451
And I hope you're
at peace with that.

35:49.495 --> 35:52.454
[tense music]

35:52.498 --> 35:53.455
♪

35:53.499 --> 35:56.458
[radio chatter]

35:56.502 --> 35:58.068
- No tracks.
No movement.

35:58.112 --> 35:59.983
- He's in here somewhere.

36:00.027 --> 36:01.637
[gunshot]

36:01.681 --> 36:03.900
- Shot fired!
- Man down!

36:03.944 --> 36:05.728
- The shot came from the south.

36:05.772 --> 36:09.689
- He's toying with us.
- He's trying to drawing us in.

36:09.732 --> 36:11.865
- Let's keep moving.

36:13.823 --> 36:15.129
- All right, move forward!
[gunshot]

36:15.173 --> 36:17.087
- Shots fired!
Two down!

36:17.131 --> 36:18.306
- Help me!

36:19.438 --> 36:20.656
- Let's form a perimeter.

36:20.700 --> 36:22.310
- Somebody help me, please!

36:23.659 --> 36:25.531
- Kristin, you're with me.

36:25.574 --> 36:27.359
- I hear you.
Are you there?

36:29.361 --> 36:32.538
- I hear you.
Help me, please!

36:32.581 --> 36:35.802
♪

36:35.845 --> 36:39.414
Help me!
Help me.

36:40.937 --> 36:43.897
Help me, please!
Help me.

36:45.115 --> 36:46.552
[gunshot]

36:49.555 --> 36:53.776
- That was a warning shot.
Take heed.

36:54.951 --> 36:58.564
- You got us out here, Wally.
What do you want us to do?

36:58.607 --> 37:00.740
- You ought to be thanking me.

37:00.783 --> 37:03.482
I'm doing your job for you.

37:03.525 --> 37:06.049
Making the world
a safer place.

37:06.093 --> 37:08.835
I want you to see
how real justice is served.

37:08.878 --> 37:11.620
- I can understand
what you're saying, Wally,

37:11.664 --> 37:14.493
but I think you know this isn't
gonna bring you any closure.

37:14.536 --> 37:16.059
- Closure is a myth.

37:16.103 --> 37:19.802
You don't just get past
what happened to me.

37:19.846 --> 37:23.850
No, a piece of me was stolen.
It's not coming back.

37:23.893 --> 37:26.418
- I believe you can
get through this.

37:26.461 --> 37:28.028
I believe you can
heal the pain.

37:28.071 --> 37:30.073
- No, I found something better.

37:30.117 --> 37:32.511
I found a way
to make the predators

37:32.554 --> 37:35.644
and the ones like you
that protect them understand.

37:35.688 --> 37:37.907
Watkins understands,
don't you?

37:37.951 --> 37:39.909
- Please, I don't want to die.

37:39.953 --> 37:46.829
♪

37:48.048 --> 37:51.573
- Nobody else needs
to get hurt, Wally.

37:51.617 --> 37:54.054
You can end this cycle
right now.

37:54.097 --> 37:55.751
The choice is yours.

37:55.795 --> 37:58.667
- There's only one way to deal
with scum like this.

37:58.711 --> 38:02.018
No jail, no rehab,
no second chances.

38:02.062 --> 38:05.108
They deserve to be put down
like the animals they are.

38:07.197 --> 38:09.461
- I can't just let you
shoot him, Wally.

38:09.504 --> 38:10.897
I swore an oath.

38:10.940 --> 38:13.073
- To protect child molesters
and rapists?

38:13.116 --> 38:16.598
- I swore an oath to protect
the citizens of this country...

38:18.600 --> 38:19.949
And that includes Farr.

38:21.908 --> 38:23.562
It includes you too, Wally.

38:23.605 --> 38:26.913
- Please--please help me.
Please.

38:26.956 --> 38:28.871
- No one's gonna
help you, Watkins.

38:28.915 --> 38:31.613
Just like no one was there
to help that nine-year-old boy.

38:31.657 --> 38:32.962
- I'm sorry.

38:33.006 --> 38:35.530
I'm sorry for what I did.
I swear to--

38:35.574 --> 38:36.792
- Shut up!

38:36.836 --> 38:38.272
Your bleating,
and your apologies

38:38.316 --> 38:39.926
aren't gonna save you now.

38:39.969 --> 38:42.494
- I don't wanna die.

38:42.537 --> 38:44.452
- Just like a true hunter,

38:44.496 --> 38:46.236
always upwind
from his prey.

38:47.629 --> 38:49.109
Now.
- Pop smoke!

38:49.152 --> 38:50.632
Pop smoke!

38:50.676 --> 38:53.853
♪

38:53.896 --> 38:54.854
[gunshot]

38:54.897 --> 38:56.769
- Shots fired!

38:58.031 --> 38:59.641
[gunshot]

39:02.644 --> 39:03.819
[gunshot]

39:06.213 --> 39:07.780
- Suspect down.

39:07.823 --> 39:09.782
- Got suspect down!
Suspect down!

39:09.825 --> 39:16.832
♪

39:19.269 --> 39:21.141
- No vitals.
Suspect is down.

39:21.184 --> 39:24.144
[tense music]

39:24.187 --> 39:28.757
♪

39:28.801 --> 39:30.803
- That smells amazing.

39:30.846 --> 39:32.631
The whole apartment
smells amazing.

39:32.674 --> 39:34.850
- The secret
is in the anchovies.

39:34.894 --> 39:37.549
You got to add 'em early
so they release the flavor.

39:39.115 --> 39:40.813
- How long did it take you
to make all this?

39:40.856 --> 39:42.597
- Not long.

39:42.641 --> 39:46.035
Now, my mother, she used
to make the pasta from scratch.

39:46.079 --> 39:48.821
Me, I bought it from the store,
'cause it's been a crazy day.

39:48.864 --> 39:50.170
- Ugh, tell me about it.

39:52.041 --> 39:55.044
- So your mother
taught you how to cook?

39:55.088 --> 39:58.657
- Yeah, she's old-school.
She was raised in Mexico City.

39:58.700 --> 40:00.963
She moved to California
when she was 14.

40:01.007 --> 40:04.010
She is the best chef
I ever met.

40:04.053 --> 40:05.838
- So your Mexican mother
taught you

40:05.881 --> 40:08.362
how to make Italian food?
- She did.

40:08.406 --> 40:10.669
She's like a chef
without borders.

40:10.712 --> 40:13.149
My dad, my brother,
and I would have dinner

40:13.193 --> 40:15.238
with her every Sunday night
before she passed.

40:15.282 --> 40:18.764
- Oh, I'm sorry. I didn't know.
When did that happen?

40:18.807 --> 40:20.809
- Five years ago.

40:20.853 --> 40:23.203
I was more worried about
my dad, but he's all good.

40:23.246 --> 40:26.206
He spends most of his time
with his retired cop buddies

40:26.249 --> 40:27.337
trading war stories.

40:27.381 --> 40:29.035
- [chuckles]

40:29.078 --> 40:30.906
- What about your mom?
How is she?

40:30.950 --> 40:34.823
- Mm, good.
Cancer is in remission.

40:34.867 --> 40:37.260
Unless you mean
my birth mother,

40:37.304 --> 40:39.306
in which case, I don't know.

40:41.047 --> 40:43.702
- Wait, you're adopted?
- Mm-hmm.

40:43.745 --> 40:45.747
- I didn't know that.
Have you ever met her?

40:46.835 --> 40:49.708
- No, I don't know
anything about her.

40:49.751 --> 40:51.797
Just this email.

40:51.840 --> 40:53.886
- You've had that email
this whole time,

40:53.929 --> 40:55.104
and haven't reached out?

40:56.279 --> 40:57.367
- I wrote an email.

40:57.411 --> 40:58.934
I asked her
a bunch of questions.

40:58.978 --> 41:00.414
I said everything
I wanted to say.

41:00.458 --> 41:02.285
- And?

41:02.329 --> 41:03.809
- And it's been sitting
in my drafts folder

41:03.852 --> 41:05.680
for the past two years.

41:05.724 --> 41:08.944
- Mm, what's stopping you
from sending it?

41:10.076 --> 41:12.426
- I don't know.
Fear?

41:12.470 --> 41:17.083
I mean, what if the answer
is worse than not knowing?

41:17.126 --> 41:19.868
- That sounds
like the old Hana.

41:19.912 --> 41:24.830
The new, seize the day Hana,
she would have sent that email.

41:26.266 --> 41:29.617
- You're right.

41:32.359 --> 41:34.796
What if I just sent it?
- What if you did?

41:36.450 --> 41:37.973
- You really think I should?

41:38.017 --> 41:40.323
- Nothing ventured,
nothing gained.

41:40.367 --> 41:47.374
♪

42:23.497 --> 42:25.194
[wolf howls]
